Properties.Description:
The Activity(s) that a specific Individual has acknowledged was identified or recorded as of the indicated date.

These criteria can change over a period of time and are represented with 'period start date/period end date' qualifications, which represented the best case for knowing this information.    If the data is only randomly sampled or recorded then you could use a single 'date' to identify its recording or effective as-of date.

Organization Criteria are a means to identify what 'positions' or 'organizational responsibilities' an individual has.   

An organization can be defined for both professional organizations ('Employment') or the family organization ("Housewife")

The Organization Criteria Type is the larger classification to which the Organization Criteria belongs.

The following are examples:

Organization Criteria:   "Housewife"
Organization Criteria Type:  "Family"

Organization Criteria:   "Manager"
Organization Criteria Type:  "Employment"

Each organization will identify, define and track a specific set of Organization Criteria to gather information about, define consumers and make decisions
